18/05/2008
TIRANA, Albania -- Prime Minister Sali Berisha says the government is interested in building a nuclear power station, in light of chronic power shortages. 
Berisha was speaking on Friday (May 16th) to the 3rd Annual Session of the Crans Montana Forum that Tirana was hosting. 
The ATA news agency reported that Berisha said Albania plans to talk with Kosovo, Macedonia and Montenegro about a joint project. 
(ATA, Albanian news - 16/05/08)
